      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/23/2/262/1",
      "text": [
        ": إِذَا قَرَأْتُمْ تَبَّتْ یَدا أَبِی لَهَبٍ وَ تَبَ فَادْعُوا عَلَی أَبِی لَهَبٍ فَإِنَّهُ کَانَ مِنَ الْمُکَذِّبِینَ الَّذِینَ یُکَذِّبُونَ بِالنَّبِیِّ ص وَ بِمَا جَاءَ بِهِ مِنْ عِنْدِ اللَّهِ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
          "1. From the previous chain from al-Hassan from Ali b. Shajarah from some of the companions Abi Abdillah (a.s.) who said: “Whenever you recite Surah Lahab, curse Abu Lahab without fail because he was such a liar that he had denied the Holy Prophet (s.a.w.s.) and whatever was revealed upon him.”"
        ]
      }
